			<name>
				<baseName xml:lang="en">Rich-manganous slags</baseName>
				<baseName xml:lang="zh">富锰渣</baseName>
			</name>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="en">HCFeMn slag; C-MnO composites; Mn-rich residue</common:synonyms>
			<common:synonyms xml:lang="zh">HCFeMn slag; C-MnO composites; Mn-rich residue</common:synonyms>
			<classificationInformation>
				<common:classification name="ILCD 1.1" classes="../ILCDClassification.xml">
					<common:class level="0">Materials production</common:class>
					<common:class level="1">Raw materials</common:class>
				</common:classification>
			</classificationInformation>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Rich-manganous slags are a by-product of smelting ores and recycled metals. They are mainly a mixture of metal oxides and silicon dioxide. They can be used as soil amendments for greenhouse gas emission reduction. Carbon has been deposited on HCFeMn slag from methane-containing gas, creating C-MnO composites. The Mn-rich residue can also be utilized as a sulfate activator to promote the pozzolanic properties of steel slag.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">富锰渣是冶炼矿石和回收金属的副产品。它们主要是金属氧化物和二氧化硅的混合物。它们可用作土壤改良剂，以减少温室气体排放。含甲烷气体中的碳沉积在 HCFeMn 熔渣上，形成 C-MnO 复合材料。富含锰的残渣还可用作硫酸盐活化剂，以促进钢渣的水青石特性。</common:generalComment>
